summary: An Ordinance authorizing the Mayor and City Comptroller to execute and deliver for and on behalf of The City of Seattle, an instrument, conveying to Milwaukee Land Company, an Iowa Corporation, all the timber, shingle bolts and wood for commercial value, now standing, lying and being upon certain lands, situated in Sections Four (4), Eight (8) and Eighteen (18), in Township Twenty-two (22) North, Range Eight (8) East, W. M., and Section Six (6) in Township Twenty-two (22) North, Range Nine (9) East, W. M., in Cedar River watershed, King County, Washington, together with the right to cut and remove the same under certain restrictions on or before a certain date.
